[{"id":27669,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5df8221c-3249-4529-8ad1-88b27a95ea61-image.png\" style=\"width: 169px; height: 191px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d252b9e2-d1a6-41c5-aecd-4a1d01cd3831-image.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 168px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9f1771c2-1830-416b-9fc1-543fc7713766-image.png\" style=\"width: 198px; height: 193px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c28d38bc-edae-48c6-91f9-405c656c945f-image.png\" style=\"width: 198px; height: 165px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fa24b981-1e51-464a-91f4-ca9a8105a734-image26.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 149px;\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/29c89d64-42d8-4329-b583-755118e1418e-image27.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 250px;\" /><br />Acid catalyzed hydrolysis of ester followed by esterification to give a six membered ring.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27691,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["Phenol","Benzoic acid","Butanal","Benzaldehyde"],"answer":3,"solution":"Benzaldehyde does not contain $\\alpha$ - hydrogen. Hence goes for cannizarro's reaction forming alcohol and acid","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":27686,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["benzophenone","acetophenone","benzoic acid","benzyl alcohol"],"answer":2,"solution":"Any aliphatic carbon with hydrogen attached to it, in combination with benzene ring, will be oxidized to benzoic acid by $\\mathrm{KMnO}_4 / \\mathrm{H}^{+}$.\nHence, (C) is correct.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":27645,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["alkylated product with ortho and para&nbsp;substitution.","secondary amine after acidic treatment.","an amide product.","positively charged nitrogen at benzene ring."],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Aniline does not undergo Friedel-crafts reaction&nbsp;due to salt formation with aluminium chloride, the Lewis acid, which is used as a catalyst, whereas&nbsp;aniline is a strong base. So, an acid-base reaction will take place. Thus, aniline reacts with <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math> to form a salt.<br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/75d7b7ac-4e45-493a-91c6-85fa0ddc3273-9711822.png\" style=\"width: 270px; height: 157px;\" /><br />Due to the positive charge on the nitrogen atom (shows <math><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> effect and it is meta directing), electrophilic substitution in the benzene ring is deactivated. Hence, the Friedel-Crafts reaction will not take place in aniline.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27662,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4ef1274b-bc04-4d37-abe6-b5c37edce7ad-image.png\" style=\"width: 127px; height: 89px;\" /></p>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9ef72861-a33d-40c7-98c6-eb7ba4414b8f-image.png\" style=\"width: 157px; height: 78px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a3e9f6a-ac83-42fd-b27a-b9009f5f7e8d-image.png\" style=\"width: 132px; height: 92px;\" />","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>RO</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CMe</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Esters are hydrolysed in basic medium(saponification)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27690,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOC}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5+\\mathrm{NaCl}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Cl}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{COONa}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COCl}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OH}+\\mathrm{NaOH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COONa}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OH}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":27657,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaBH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>LiAlH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>","Alkaline <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HCl</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>Zn</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>Hg</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;in presence of acidic medium shows oxidation reaction.&nbsp;</p><p>It converts carbon into acid if carbon is connected to benzene group directly and having at least one hydrogen with it then it can be converted into acid otherwise not. As shown below:</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b447cb72-1ac4-4260-ae3f-c65b174dfe44-image.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 253px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27665,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mrow></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>6</mn></msub></math> is very selective and usually used to reduce acid into alcohol.</p><p>Borane is commonly used for the reduction of carboxylic acids in the presence of esters, lactones, amides, halides and other functional groups. In addition, borane rapidly reduces aldehydes, ketones, and alkenes.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27670,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/025580cc-a238-437f-92b5-943bc721531d-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 129px;\" /></p><br />&nbsp;","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4119bec6-944a-4c78-bdad-fc6b091046e2-image.png\" style=\"width: 130px; height: 140px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/159706ba-fa12-4622-9789-c72c8bb39290-image.png\" style=\"width: 130px; height: 112px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/187c93d4-fcc8-40bd-93af-aeff698192fa-image.png\" style=\"width: 130px; height: 130px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4c014ab9-cf3a-401a-99f0-dc350a68c76e-image12.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 106px;\" /><br />Alkaline <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>4</mn></math> oxidise&nbsp;benzylic carbon to the carboxylic acid.</p><p>Alkenes react with acidified potassium permanganate. Potassium Permanganate is a strong oxidant, and will initially convert the double bond to two alcohol (OH) groups.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27671,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></math> convert ester into alcohol by reduction, it does not reduce <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></math> bond between carbon atoms.<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/357f8ad0-6dc7-4e2a-b979-7f3cabea8072-image.png\" style=\"width: 804px; height: 90px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27650,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3c6661f2-a5d2-4615-a73e-da4c4be666f1-67f8c20e-d492-410c-bed9-f0fb2bea1948-image.png\" style=\"width: 429px; height: 72px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/30e0e91e-6261-4879-b0cc-1b21fb009ed8-image.png\" style=\"width: 492px; height: 45px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/82f54392-b390-455c-860a-ab7388c5ced3-779c9799-85f0-4040-8160-0b1cfa14df47-image.png\" style=\"width: 402px; height: 46px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7244ae75-8c6b-49ee-8a0c-549e2592b9d7-image.png\" style=\"width: 410px; height: 50px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/71fedead-2724-448d-b2e6-d2cad180ab1e-image.png\" style=\"width: 624px; height: 124px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27620,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["2-Chloropropanoic acid","3-Chloropropanoic acid","1-Chloropropane","2-Chloropropane"],"answer":0,"solution":"Step 1: Hydrolysis of the nitrile.<br>Propanenitrile on basic hydrolysis followed by acidic workup gives propanoic acid:<br>$CH_3-CH_2-C \\equiv N \\xrightarrow[(ii)\\ H_3O^+]{(i)\\ OH^-/H_2O/\\Delta} CH_3-CH_2-COOH$<br><br>Step 2: Hell$-$Volhard$-$Zelinsky (HVZ) reaction.<br>Propanoic acid has an $sp^3$ $\\alpha$-carbon bearing two $\\alpha$-hydrogens. In the HVZ reaction, $Cl_2$ in the presence of red phosphorus selectively replaces one $\\alpha$-hydrogen by chlorine, giving the $\\alpha$-chloro acid after aqueous workup:<br>$CH_3-CH_2-COOH \\xrightarrow[(iv)\\ H_2O]{(iii)\\ Cl_2/\\text{Red P}} CH_3-CH(Cl)-COOH$<br><br>Hence, the major product $P$ is $2$-chloropropanoic acid, which corresponds to option $(1)$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (05 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27675,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bd4fe45d-edd3-41cf-81fd-9426eb480b2c-image.png\" style=\"width: 253px; height: 84px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a6bf07c-1cdd-4efc-9e85-d7a49c35f7f6-image.png\" style=\"width: 205px; height: 109px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8079f788-2eea-4888-b7e7-b0b87738ec06-image.png\" style=\"width: 165px; height: 118px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/85f14677-163d-47cb-8f55-e9c3dde2a75f-image.png\" style=\"width: 181px; height: 101px;\" /></p>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b3e7fc2f-8928-47df-b2c2-9b058be72161-408e3b49-b5e9-475a-a384-c699f688951f-image.png\" style=\"width: 421px; height: 303px;\" /></p><p><br />&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27660,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>COOH</mi></math>&nbsp;group present in</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/21ddb3e9-c950-4dc5-8e6c-088424aea058-01bd4eb6-60d5-499f-983a-bf9d87e7851f-image.png\" style=\"width: 153px; height: 458px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27631,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8evzpsfmHf1SfX-9Z2jKsRKh_vc2coxvx1lsFz2ynb0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/BSz82pxRJ4SOPGbvtGLjSONldY5ClRHJGcsdZZeFUkU.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/qFGR5HY7dMXuftEThJVGnqj47mQfO16zCCg6CJO03Ks.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/AGROpBrwiHF3bZBHnZVkMNkGmXlh0Lxz12pJvxNeAWA.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/DGY025fZ8PxAZYpU_GeGwyXwZ0KnSUsJyUcyfpFK_Kc.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/GXDOletxQSDWjOWEN34Tp_1qGJluSYfiZONibJKOAfg.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27653,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9b487b52-6128-48ab-902c-062b8b7e310e-image.png\" style=\"width: 325px; height: 132px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8094e1cf-8b9e-4030-b496-5095b35bc001-image.png\" style=\"width: 325px; height: 132px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9f8312d8-a1bf-42d6-97ee-e8bce0112cc9-image.png\" style=\"width: 308px; height: 132px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2faa9938-925f-40ee-869a-8485e17b09cd-image.png\" style=\"width: 362px; height: 132px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f050d57a-e0e1-4f4f-ad39-0053d184d0af-image.png\" style=\"width: 869px; height: 323px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27643,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1bf873c2-ea5c-4235-af37-d95927109697-image.png\" style=\"width: 346px; height: 70px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/94f580d1-c56f-4df0-9df5-9b7c80e4b7e4-image.png\" style=\"width: 352px; height: 90px;\" /></p>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2dda7458-854d-4202-9b7f-dbbe05b5ec08-image.png\" style=\"width: 361px; height: 90px;\" />","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f0b799e6-8b68-4dc0-9bc9-d3eec561a68b-image.png\" style=\"width: 316px; height: 60px;\" /></p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>DiBAL-H is&nbsp;Diisobutylaluminium hydride, which is a very useful reducing agent. It is used for selectively converting ester or nitriles into respective aldehydes. It does not affect other groups like aldehyde or double bond.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4ef7aab7-f5fc-4422-8d02-76f9e36b3c9a-dec4377f-1cd8-4a10-ae36-907c1a68790d-image.png\" style=\"width: 396px; height: 231px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27661,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>OH</mi><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><msub><mi>CrO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></mrow></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfrac><mrow><mi>Pd</mi><mfenced><mi>II</mi></mfenced><mo>/</mo><mi>Cu</mi><mfenced><mi>II</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>CN</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)&#160;</mo><mi>DIBAL</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>)</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#62;</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>OH</mi><mfrac><mi>Cu</mi><mrow><mn>573</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#62;</mo></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Ethyl alcohol on oxidation with acidified chromium oxide forms acetic acid. The reaction is as follows:</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/869e492d-5793-4fe3-bdc2-72e1f8527665-image.png\" style=\"width: 420px; height: 159px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27624,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c_n0EjvFgKMuxdALDlJFAU2HhP58wehMW_XMTXwaDME.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/P7wbZ-bHgm1Ui0BqxGlSgAq4vDkTS6UpQi0ZVOcSyGI.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/v4apkzB6hZn1arP9pp-AkvyLpTACuDz5Zi-5ER28AaU.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dub3OcY7XY4044kcOJMKLFUeGnxCdNzHByLN7Zn4Jog.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"Concept - Those compounds which are more acidic than $\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{CO}_3$ can gives effervescence of $\\mathrm{CO}_2$ with aq. $\\mathrm{NaHCO}_3$.<br />Release $\\mathrm{CO}_2 \\uparrow$ gas with aq. NaHCO 3<br />$\\Rightarrow[\\text { A.S. }]_{\\text {Comp. }} \\gt [\\text { A.S. }]_{\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{CO}_3}$<br />$\\rightarrow$ Option 1,2 and 3 gives effervescence of $\\mathrm{CO}_2$ gas with $\\mathrm{NaHCO}_3$<br />$\\rightarrow$ Option (4) Not gives $\\mathrm{CO}_2$ gas with $\\mathrm{NaHCO}_3$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27644,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/668ce3ce-2388-4c15-9278-b1d11b49d774-image.png\" style=\"width: 288px; height: 100px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8e8e7a64-b2dd-44c8-8317-2f3b163963a5-image.png\" style=\"width: 215px; height: 120px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CHBr</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3224c753-b644-4cf5-ad0b-a9b19eb2ee34-image.png\" style=\"width: 84px; height: 120px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a6646ac4-6585-4b91-b897-613471f0e720-image.png\" style=\"width: 85px; height: 120px;\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CHBr</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Based on the percentage composition of the elements given the molecular formula of the compound is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>8</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>9</mn></msub><mi>Br</mi></math></p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fc1671c4-65f6-42ef-9f4b-924a0c4a6842-dbe.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 156px;\" /></p><p>And the degree of unsaturation or double bond equivalent of&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>8</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>9</mn></msub><mi>Br</mi></math>&nbsp;is 4.</p><p>It is mentioned that A is optically active and gives pale yellow precipitate with&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>AgNO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>.</p><p>Hence, the structures of A and B can be deduced based on the following reactions.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1cfc77f5-782b-4944-9836-8f18e2d22e25-13-7-20223.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 378px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27692,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CHO}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{COOH}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{LiAl}^{\\mathrm{H}}{ }_4$ can reduce $\\mathrm{COOH}$ group and not the double bond\n$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{COOH} \\underset{\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}}{\\stackrel{\\mathrm{LAH}}{\\longrightarrow}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":27694,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{COCl}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CHO}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CHCOOH}$","$\\mathrm{ClCH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{COOH}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/RnKOv31ZXIAr5RihYMyaBE3hQ_f5se7UqkY3V62OVnE.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":27639,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/39c1e85b-cc77-47b8-9509-33046aee8348-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 143px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6ae73b4d-ac46-49db-a8ed-a07ad83d8189-image.png\" style=\"width: 248px; height: 150px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a7a995b2-3858-4c56-98a0-7cf433aedf36-image.png\" style=\"width: 248px; height: 131px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/faa48d79-06f6-40e5-bdec-262b38be2c9b-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 102px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>In the first step bromine attacks the carbon-carbon double bond by electrophilic addition reaction mechanism and forms the bromonium&nbsp;cyclic intermediate. In the presence of sodium bicarbonate carboxylic acid group present in the reactant&nbsp;converts to carboxylate ion. This carboxylate ion opens the cyclic bromonium ion ring and forms the desired product.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bdaeac43-97bd-4440-b424-f4895151620b-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 228px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27648,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>LiAlH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>MnO</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaBH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>When benzoic acid is heated with formic acid in presence of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Mno</mi></math>, benzaldehyde is obtained.</p><p>The reaction is given below, along with benzaldehyde, carbondioxide and water are also obtained.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>5</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>HCOOH</mi><munderover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>Heat</mi><mi>MnO</mi></munderover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>5</mn></msub><mi>CHO</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27676,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>III</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>III</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>IV</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"The rate of hydrolysis will depend on how likely a molecule is to accepting &nbsp;<math><mi>O</mi><msup><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; ions. Rate of hydrolysis&nbsp;<math><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>M</mi></math>&nbsp; effect or <math><mo>-</mo><mi>I</mi></math> of ester.&nbsp;<math><mo>-</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>I</mi></math>. <math><mo>-</mo><mi>N</mi><msub><mrow><mi>O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>&nbsp; is a strong <math><mi>E</mi><mi>W</mi><mi>G</mi></math> (Electron withdrawing group),<math><mo>-</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>l</mi></math> is a weak <math><mi>E</mi><mi>W</mi><mi>G</mi></math> and <math><mi>O</mi><mi>C</mi><msub><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math> is an <math><mi>E</mi><mi>D</mi><mi>G</mi></math>(Electron donating group).","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27689,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{PhCOOH}$","$\\mathrm{O}-\\mathrm{NO}_2 \\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_4 \\mathrm{COOH}$","$\\mathrm{p}-\\mathrm{NO}_2 \\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_4 \\mathrm{COOH}$","$\\mathrm{m}-\\mathrm{NO}_2 \\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_4 \\mathrm{COOH}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":27681,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/71c6330d-31e4-4fdc-8ffa-a9a085be0624-image.png\" style=\"width: 122px; height: 75px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/64e71f11-9d15-486e-a8b5-e0f7fa9c3a5a-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 75px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/adbeb9f2-d1b3-409c-9e75-3953380b66b8-image.png\" style=\"width: 121px; height: 75px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/33e701db-30f2-4d96-81de-505b434c4ac0-image.png\" style=\"width: 110px; height: 135px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/448bb025-0c1c-47f1-8abf-c266f31a6e64-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 124px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (10 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27636,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5a60e685-6dd7-4661-b430-0a8d5f8da08e.png\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 149px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5760d412-4ce2-4321-9c56-5a17da992a89.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 163px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/43e14125-985a-41d6-96f7-d05813970d5f.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 162px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a56cfc97-addf-48d2-9080-bc3762d93757.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 169px;\"/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Reaction of aniline sulphonic acid with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaNO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi></math> gives diazo ester sulphonic acid. Which on further treatment with naphthalene derivative undergoes diazo coupling reaction to give red azo dye.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4794da58-c530-4672-ad6a-6a7ebfa24171.png\" style=\"width: 700px; height: 270px;\"/></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2cca182a-c4db-4896-828d-ccf85b1c2e1e.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 530px;\"/></p><p>This is known as Griess-Ilosvay test. </p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27668,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c86c2604-2ed7-42fa-95c6-5555ed885721-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 87px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5f55fc5b-8b17-48b5-a19b-0a957eb535d2-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 94px;\" />","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c68ca53f-1183-428c-880b-9b3f793be83b-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 138px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ed90ecfb-136c-4380-a3b1-ba3e80ca5e16-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 74px;\" /><br />as <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> is a better nucleophile than <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27635,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/14d9c468-f21c-42de-9220-a2b609f24fed.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 156px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c7b403d1-ddae-4a9e-aaf5-f70d86a78d4d.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 111px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e6884dcf-f016-4c6b-9661-bcc32ecda062.png\" style=\"width: 249px; height: 240px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/08ee4d77-5310-4c7c-b87a-ef73d15176c8.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 138px;\"/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><strong>Freidel-Crafts Acylation:</strong></p><ul> <li>Friedel-Crafts acylation reaction is a type of reaction where an acyl group is added to an aromatic ring.</li> <li>This reaction occurs in the presence of an acid chloride <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>Cl</mi></math> and a Lewis acid catalyst like Aluminium chloride <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>AlCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>.</li> <li>Friedel-Crafts acylation reaction, changes the aromatic ring into a aromatic ketone.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/de8f3d55-e97a-44e6-8539-3bf23280d899.png\" style=\"width: 704px; height: 521px;\"/></li></ul>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null}]